1
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,863
I should have known
that you would be here,

2
00:01:24,895 --> 00:01:26,521
Professor McGonagall.

3
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:39,896
Good evening, Professor Dumbledore.

4
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,135
Are the rumors true,

5
00:01:45,475 --> 00:01:46,365
Albus?

6
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:48,722
I am afraid so, professor.

7
00:01:49,389 --> 00:01:50,265
The good...

8
00:01:50,740 --> 00:01:51,935
and the bad.

9
00:01:52,475 --> 00:01:53,435
And the boy?

10
00:01:53,904 --> 00:01:55,311
Hagrid is bringing him.

11
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,105
Do you think it wise,

12
00:01:57,129 --> 00:02:00,003
to trust Hagrid with something
as important as this?

13
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,443
Oh, professor,

14
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:03,932
I would trust Hagrid, with my life.

15
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,531
Professor Dumbledore, sir.

16
00:02:25,918 --> 00:02:27,363
Professor McGonagall.

17
00:02:28,214 --> 00:02:30,221
No problems, I trust Hagrid?

18
00:02:30,668 --> 00:02:31,707
No, sir.

19
00:02:32,525 --> 00:02:35,753
Little tyke fell asleep just
as we were flying over Bristol.

20
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,090
Try not to wake him.

21
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:41,887
There you go.

22
00:02:48,039 --> 00:02:48,965
Albus,

23
00:02:49,532 --> 00:02:51,493
do you really think it's safe,

24
00:02:51,614 --> 00:02:53,272
leaving him with these people?

25
00:02:53,297 --> 00:02:54,621
I have watched them all day.

26
00:02:54,645 --> 00:02:57,687
They are the worst sort of Muggles,
imaginable.

27
00:02:58,825 --> 00:03:01,739
They really are...
The only family he has.

28
00:03:03,059 --> 00:03:04,672
This boy will be famous.

29
00:03:04,926 --> 00:03:08,307
There won't be a child in our world
who doesn't know his name.

30
00:03:08,332 --> 00:03:09,270
Exactly.

31
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,221
He is far better off,

32
00:03:11,245 --> 00:03:13,010
growing up away from all of that.

33
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,346
Until he is ready.

34
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:32,951
There, there Hagrid.

35
00:03:33,568 --> 00:03:35,984
It's not really goodbye, after all.

36
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,906
Good luck...

37
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:52,758
Harry Potter.

38
00:04:11,163 --> 00:04:13,218
Up. Get up!

39
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:17,710
Now!

40
00:04:32,079 --> 00:04:33,386
Wake up cousin!

41
00:04:33,613 --> 00:04:34,984
We are going to the zoo!

42
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,359
Here he comes,

43
00:04:48,383 --> 00:04:51,960
the birthday boy.
Happy birthday son.

44
00:04:53,998 --> 00:04:56,943
Why don't you just cook the breakfast,
and try not to burn anything.

45
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,161
Yes, Aunt Petunia.

46
00:04:58,185 --> 00:05:01,717
I want everything to be perfect...

47
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:05,299
for my Dudley's special day!

48
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,419
Hurry up!

49
00:05:06,972 --> 00:05:08,087
Bring my coffee boy.

50
00:05:08,111 --> 00:05:09,261
Yes Uncle Vernon.

51
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,468
Aren't they wonderful darling?

52
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,139
How many are there?

53
00:05:18,234 --> 00:05:19,307
36.

54
00:05:19,331 --> 00:05:20,437
Counted them myself.

55
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:23,899
36? But last year...
last year I had 37!

56
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:26,481
Yeah but some of them
are quite a bit bigger than last year's.

57
00:05:26,482 --> 00:05:28,187
I don't care how big they are!

58
00:05:28,212 --> 00:05:30,157
Oh, now, now, now.
This is what we are going to do...

59
00:05:30,182 --> 00:05:31,319
is that when we go out,

60
00:05:31,452 --> 00:05:33,238
we are going to buy you
two new presents.

61
00:05:33,684 --> 00:05:35,032
How is that pumpkin?

62
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:39,577
It should be a lovely day at the zoo.

63
00:05:39,601 --> 00:05:41,779
I am really looking forward to it.

64
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,740
I am warning you now boy.

65
00:05:48,179 --> 00:05:50,129
Any funny business,

66
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,578
any at all,

67
00:05:51,984 --> 00:05:53,773
and you won't have any meals,

68
00:05:53,907 --> 00:05:54,906
for a week.

69
00:05:55,428 --> 00:05:56,412
Get in.

70
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,703
Make it move.

71
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,656
Move!

72
00:06:11,585 --> 00:06:13,288
Move!
He is asleep!

73
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,569
He is boring.

74
00:06:19,241 --> 00:06:20,413
Sorry about him.

75
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,453
He doesn't understand what it's like,

76
00:06:22,727 --> 00:06:24,719
lying there day after day...

77
00:06:25,263 --> 00:06:27,922
watching people press
their ugly faces in on you.

78
00:06:31,754 --> 00:06:33,196
Can you hear me?

79
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:37,969
It's just,

80
00:06:38,353 --> 00:06:40,392
I have never talked to a snake before.

81
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:42,360
Do you...

82
00:06:42,929 --> 00:06:43,808
I mean,

83
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:46,008
do you talk to people often?

84
00:06:48,138 --> 00:06:49,355
You are from Burma, are not you?

85
00:06:50,094 --> 00:06:51,415
Was it nice there?

86
00:06:51,829 --> 00:06:53,055
Do you miss your family?

87
00:06:56,759 --> 00:06:57,780
I see.

88
00:06:58,422 --> 00:06:59,699
That's me as well.

89
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,770
I never knew my parents either.

90
00:07:02,050 --> 00:07:03,536
Mummy, Dad, come here!

91
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,871
You won't believe
what this snake is doing!

92
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,243
Thanks.

93
00:07:32,014 --> 00:07:33,189
Anytime.

94
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:38,009
Snake!

95
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:55,713
Mum! Mummy!

96
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,599
Help me!

97
00:07:57,844 --> 00:07:59,524
Please, please.
My darling boy!

98
00:07:59,556 --> 00:08:01,323
Help me! Help me!
How did you get in there?

99
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,520
Who did this? How did you get in there?

100
00:08:03,544 --> 00:08:05,204
Is there a snake?

101
00:08:11,359 --> 00:08:12,605
It's alright, sweetheart.

102
00:08:12,629 --> 00:08:15,046
We will get you out of these cold clothes.

103
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,696
What happened?

104
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:21,222
I swear, I don't know!

105
00:08:21,817 --> 00:08:24,033
One minute the glass was there
and then it was gone,

106
00:08:24,057 --> 00:08:25,238
it was like magic.

107
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:32,743
There is no such thing as magic.

108
00:08:46,909 --> 00:08:48,560
And smile!

109
00:08:50,678 --> 00:08:53,271
Vernon, just look at him!
I can't believe it!

110
00:08:53,592 --> 00:08:56,199
In just a week, he will be off to Smeltings.

111
00:08:56,357 --> 00:08:58,067
Caveat Smeltonia.

112
00:08:58,506 --> 00:09:00,199
Proudest moment of my life.

113
00:09:00,496 --> 00:09:02,193
Will I have to wear that too?

114
00:09:04,151 --> 00:09:05,491
What? You?

115
00:09:05,765 --> 00:09:07,001
Go to Smeltings?

116
00:09:12,371 --> 00:09:13,791
Don't be so stupid!

117
00:09:13,815 --> 00:09:15,815
You are going to go to the state
school where you belong.

118
00:09:16,338 --> 00:09:19,299
This is what you will going to be wearing
when I finish dyeing it.

119
00:09:19,830 --> 00:09:21,758
That's Dudley's old uniform.

120
00:09:21,782 --> 00:09:24,075
It will fit me like bits
of old elephant skin.

121
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:25,893
It will fit you well enough.

122
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:28,055
Go get the post.

123
00:09:28,555 --> 00:09:29,425
Go!

124
00:10:01,047 --> 00:10:03,289
Marge is ill. Ate a funny whelk.

125
00:10:03,398 --> 00:10:04,967
Dad, look! Harry's got a letter!

126
00:10:04,991 --> 00:10:06,476
Hey, give it back! It's mine!

127
00:10:07,031 --> 00:10:09,570
Yours? Who would be writing to you?

128
00:10:40,792 --> 00:10:44,363
No more mail through this letterbox.

129
00:10:57,636 --> 00:10:59,425
Have a lovely day at the office, dear.

130
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,181
Shoo! Go on.

131
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,882
Fine day, Sunday.

132
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,550
In my opinion, best day of the week.

133
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:11,186
Why is that, Dudley?

134
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,138
Because there is no post on Sundays?

135
00:12:14,319 --> 00:12:15,795
Right you are Harry!

136
00:12:17,029 --> 00:12:18,388
No post on Sunday.

137
00:12:21,111 --> 00:12:23,689
No blasted letters today!

138
00:12:24,143 --> 00:12:25,315
No, sir.

139
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:28,235
Not one single bloody letter.

140
00:12:28,259 --> 00:12:29,360
Not one!

141
00:12:38,756 --> 00:12:40,039
No sir.

142
00:12:40,343 --> 00:12:42,790
Not one blasted miserable...

143
00:12:53,812 --> 00:12:55,916
No! Make it stop please!

144
00:12:58,414 --> 00:13:00,714
Stop it! Stop it! Stop it!

145
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,406
Mummy, what's happening?

146
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,154
Give me that!

147
00:13:13,162 --> 00:13:15,076
Give me that letter!

148
00:13:17,759 --> 00:13:18,540
Get off!

149
00:13:23,288 --> 00:13:24,500
They are my letters!

150
00:13:25,085 --> 00:13:26,272
Let go of me!

151
00:13:28,257 --> 00:13:29,380
That's it!

152
00:13:30,046 --> 00:13:31,397
We are going away!

153
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:33,384
Far away!

154
00:13:33,944 --> 00:13:35,623
Where they can't find us!

155
00:13:35,945 --> 00:13:37,990
Daddy is gone mad, hasn't he?

156
00:14:13,989 --> 00:14:15,129
Make a wish, Harry.

157
00:14:32,328 --> 00:14:33,226
Who is there?

158
00:14:46,589 --> 00:14:48,081
Sorry about that.

159
00:14:55,944 --> 00:14:58,052
I demand that you leave at once, Sir!

160
00:14:58,076 --> 00:14:59,636
You are breaking and entering!

161
00:15:03,351 --> 00:15:06,043
Dry up, Dursley, you great prune.

162
00:15:11,490 --> 00:15:14,240
Mind I have not seen you
since you was a baby Harry but...

163
00:15:14,745 --> 00:15:18,088
you are a bit more along than I would have
expected particularly around the middle.

164
00:15:19,974 --> 00:15:21,685
I am, I am not Harry.

165
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:25,704
I-I am.

166
00:15:26,794 --> 00:15:28,396
Well, of course you are.

167
00:15:29,285 --> 00:15:30,621
Got something for you.

168
00:15:30,796 --> 00:15:33,170
Afraid I might have sat on it
at somepoint but...

169
00:15:33,545 --> 00:15:35,575
I imagine it will taste fine just the same.

170
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:41,256
Baked it myself, words and all.

171
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,123
Thank you.

172
00:15:49,148 --> 00:15:51,678
It's not every day that your young man
turns 11, now is it?

173
00:15:51,764 --> 00:15:52,506
Hey...

174
00:16:08,395 --> 00:16:10,124
Excuse me,

175
00:16:11,277 --> 00:16:12,636
who are you?

176
00:16:12,828 --> 00:16:14,253
Rubeus Hagrid,

177
00:16:14,574 --> 00:16:17,386
Keeper of Keys and Grounds at Hogwarts.

178
00:16:18,044 --> 00:16:20,092
Of course, you know all about Hogwarts.

179
00:16:20,405 --> 00:16:21,636
Sorry, no.

180
00:16:22,351 --> 00:16:23,095
No?

181
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:26,730
Blimey, Harry didn't you ever wonder
where your mum and dad learned it all?

182
00:16:27,207 --> 00:16:28,222
Learnt what?

183
00:16:29,050 --> 00:16:30,543
You are a wizard, Harry.

184
00:16:32,921 --> 00:16:34,887
I am a what?
A wizard.

185
00:16:35,112 --> 00:16:36,775
And a thumping good one, I would wager,

186
00:16:36,799 --> 00:16:38,238
once you are trained up little.

187
00:16:38,263 --> 00:16:38,986
No.

188
00:16:39,220 --> 00:16:40,783
You have made a mistake, I mean...

189
00:16:41,488 --> 00:16:42,156
I...

190
00:16:42,398 --> 00:16:43,365
can't be a-a...

191
00:16:43,658 --> 00:16:44,628
a wizard.

192
00:16:45,151 --> 00:16:45,910
I mean I am...

193
00:16:46,136 --> 00:16:46,952
just...

194
00:16:47,385 --> 00:16:48,109
Harry.

195
00:16:48,886 --> 00:16:49,925
Just Harry.

196
00:16:51,029 --> 00:16:52,541
Well, Just Harry,

197
00:16:53,315 --> 00:16:54,729
did you ever make anything happen?

198
00:16:55,188 --> 00:16:57,338
Anything you could not explain,
when you were angry or...

199
00:16:57,471 --> 00:16:58,493
or scared?

200
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,608
Dear Mr. Potter,

201
00:17:17,958 --> 00:17:19,497
We are pleased to inform you

202
00:17:19,522 --> 00:17:21,362
that you have been accepted
at Hogwarts School

203
00:17:21,386 --> 00:17:22,770
of Witchcraft and Wizardry.

204
00:17:22,926 --> 00:17:25,160
He will not be going there, I tell you!

205
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:28,068
We swore when we took him in
we would put a stop to all this rubbish.

206
00:17:28,157 --> 00:17:28,953
You knew?

207
00:17:30,183 --> 00:17:32,487
You knew all along
and you never told me?

208
00:17:32,620 --> 00:17:33,540
Of course we knew.

209
00:17:34,229 --> 00:17:35,690
How could you not be?

210
00:17:35,974 --> 00:17:36,710
My...

211
00:17:36,997 --> 00:17:39,130
perfect sister being who she was.

212
00:17:39,528 --> 00:17:42,299
Oh, my mother and father were so...

213
00:17:42,479 --> 00:17:44,971
proud the day she got her letter.

214
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:48,264
We have a witch in the family.

215
00:17:48,369 --> 00:17:49,455
Isn't it wonderful?

216
00:17:50,295 --> 00:17:52,933
I was the only one to see her
for what she was.

217
00:17:54,312 --> 00:17:55,659
A freak!

218
00:17:56,329 --> 00:17:57,898
Then she met that Potter,

219
00:17:58,073 --> 00:18:00,943
and then she had you
and I knew you would be the same.

220
00:18:00,967 --> 00:18:03,193
Just as strange, just as...

221
00:18:04,115 --> 00:18:05,294
abnormal.

222
00:18:05,398 --> 00:18:06,365
And then, if you please,

223
00:18:06,568 --> 00:18:08,409
she went and got herself blown up!

224
00:18:08,433 --> 00:18:10,491
And we got landed with you.

225
00:18:10,582 --> 00:18:11,495
Blown up?

226
00:18:11,959 --> 00:18:14,584
You told me my parents
died in a car crash.

227
00:18:14,835 --> 00:18:16,041
A car crash?

228
00:18:16,913 --> 00:18:19,209
A car crash killed Lily and James Potter?

229
00:18:19,234 --> 00:18:20,379
We had to say something.

230
00:18:20,403 --> 00:18:22,006
It's an outrage!

231
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:23,466
It's a scandal!

232
00:18:23,522 --> 00:18:24,920
He will not be going.

233
00:18:26,135 --> 00:18:29,466
Oh, and I suppose a great Muggle like yourself
is going to stop him, are you?

234
00:18:29,697 --> 00:18:30,630
Muggle?

235
00:18:30,942 --> 00:18:32,266
Non-magic folk.

236
00:18:32,290 --> 00:18:34,658
This boy's had his name down
ever since he were born.

237
00:18:35,126 --> 00:18:36,478
He is going to the finest school,

238
00:18:36,502 --> 00:18:39,225
of witchcraft and wizardry
in the world, and...

239
00:18:39,335 --> 00:18:41,275
he will be under the finest headmaster,

240
00:18:41,299 --> 00:18:42,985
that Hogwarts has ever seen,

241
00:18:43,282 --> 00:18:45,173
Albus Dumbledore.

242
00:18:45,365 --> 00:18:49,341
I will not pay to have some crackpot
old fool teach him magic tricks.

243
00:18:50,302 --> 00:18:51,118
Never...

244
00:18:51,701 --> 00:18:54,232
insult Albus Dumbledore...

245
00:18:54,568 --> 00:18:55,966
in front of me.

246
00:19:05,375 --> 00:19:06,773
What's that tail!

247
00:19:09,383 --> 00:19:10,852
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

248
00:19:15,135 --> 00:19:15,893
Oh...

249
00:19:16,042 --> 00:19:17,728
I would appreciate it
if you didn't tell anyone...

250
00:19:18,088 --> 00:19:19,424
at Hogwarts about that.

251
00:19:20,619 --> 00:19:22,608
Strickly speaking,
I am not allowed to do magic.

252
00:19:22,765 --> 00:19:23,260
Ok.

253
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:27,488
We are a bit behind schedule.

254
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:28,496
Best be off.

255
00:19:35,267 --> 00:19:37,104
Unless you'd rather stay, of course.

256
00:19:52,442 --> 00:19:54,181
First year students will require...

257
00:19:54,478 --> 00:19:56,220
three sets of plain work robes...

258
00:19:56,663 --> 00:19:57,696
one wand.

259
00:19:58,620 --> 00:20:00,220
Essential bit of equipment, Harry.

260
00:20:02,014 --> 00:20:03,607
One pair of dragon hide gloves.

261
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:06,810
Hagrid, do they mean from a real dragon?

262
00:20:06,897 --> 00:20:08,677
Oh, they don't mean a penguin, do they?

263
00:20:11,322 --> 00:20:12,157
Crikey.

264
00:20:12,735 --> 00:20:13,867
I would love a dragon.

265
00:20:13,992 --> 00:20:15,368
You would like a dragon?

266
00:20:15,711 --> 00:20:17,830
Vastly misunderstood beasts, Harry.

267
00:20:18,329 --> 00:20:19,946
Vastly misunderstood.

268
00:20:27,366 --> 00:20:30,139
All students must be equipped with...

269
00:20:30,818 --> 00:20:33,412
one standard size 2 pewter cauldron...

270
00:20:34,050 --> 00:20:35,681
and may bring if they desire,

271
00:20:35,931 --> 00:20:38,569
either an owl, a cat or a toad.

272
00:20:40,003 --> 00:20:41,647
Can we find all this in London?

273
00:20:42,615 --> 00:20:44,132
If you know where to go.

274
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:09,423
Hagrid!

275
00:21:09,776 --> 00:21:11,010
The usual, I presume?

276
00:21:11,165 --> 00:21:14,143
No thanks, Tom.
I am on official Hogwarts business.

277
00:21:15,211 --> 00:21:17,898
Just helping young Harry here
buy his school supplies.

278
00:21:18,501 --> 00:21:19,683
Bless my soul.

279
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:21,422
It's Harry Potter!

280
00:21:26,348 --> 00:21:27,858
Welcome back, Mr. Potter.

281
00:21:28,210 --> 00:21:29,162
Welcome back.

282
00:21:30,071 --> 00:21:31,651
Doris Crockford, Mr Potter.

283
00:21:31,675 --> 00:21:34,225
I can't believe I am meeting you at last.

284
00:21:34,809 --> 00:21:35,670
Harry...

285
00:21:36,381 --> 00:21:37,117
Potter.

286
00:21:38,084 --> 00:21:40,208
Can't tell you how pleased
I am to meet you.

287
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:41,330
Hello professor.

288
00:21:41,354 --> 00:21:42,685
I didn't see you there.

289
00:21:43,016 --> 00:21:44,666
Harry, this is Professor Quirrell.

290
00:21:44,997 --> 00:21:47,377
He will be your Defense Against
the Dark Arts teacher,

291
00:21:47,401 --> 00:21:48,396
at Hogwarts.

292
00:21:48,421 --> 00:21:49,763
Oh, nice to meet you.

293
00:21:50,893 --> 00:21:51,840
Fearfully...

294
00:21:52,037 --> 00:21:53,427
fascinating subject.

295
00:21:54,279 --> 00:21:57,638
N... Not that you need it, eh... Potter.

296
00:21:59,732 --> 00:22:00,682
Yes well,

297
00:22:00,706 --> 00:22:02,055
must be going now.

298
00:22:02,517 --> 00:22:03,984
Lots to buy.

299
00:22:04,249 --> 00:22:05,086
Goodbye.

300
00:22:08,641 --> 00:22:11,891
See Harry? You are famous.
But why am I famous Hagrid?

301
00:22:12,449 --> 00:22:13,862
All those people back there,

302
00:22:14,113 --> 00:22:15,828
how is it they know who I am?

303
00:22:16,095 --> 00:22:18,827
I am not sure I am exactly the right person
to tell you that, Harry.

304
00:22:36,863 --> 00:22:37,873
Welcome Harry,

305
00:22:38,082 --> 00:22:39,418
to Diagon Alley.

306
00:22:56,995 --> 00:22:59,014
Here is where you will get
your quills and your ink.

307
00:22:59,850 --> 00:23:02,631
And over there, all your bits and bobs
for doing your wizardry.

308
00:23:28,845 --> 00:23:30,766
It's a worldclass racing broom.

309
00:23:30,979 --> 00:23:31,815
Look at it!

310
00:23:31,971 --> 00:23:33,969
The new Nimbus 2000!

311
00:23:35,140 --> 00:23:37,054
It's the fastest model yet.

312
00:23:42,108 --> 00:23:43,160
But Hagrid,

313
00:23:43,363 --> 00:23:45,037
how am I to pay for all this?

314
00:23:45,447 --> 00:23:46,712
I have not any money.

315
00:23:46,963 --> 00:23:48,540
Well there is your money, Harry.

316
00:23:48,564 --> 00:23:50,173
Gringotts, the wizard bank.

317
00:23:50,533 --> 00:23:52,627
Tain't no safer place, not one.

318
00:23:52,861 --> 00:23:54,337
Except perhaps Hogwarts.

319
00:24:08,633 --> 00:24:09,618
Hagrid?

320
00:24:10,626 --> 00:24:12,649
What exactly are these things?

321
00:24:12,933 --> 00:24:14,172
They are goblins, Harry.

322
00:24:14,821 --> 00:24:17,915
Clever as they come goblins
but not the most friendly of beasts.

323
00:24:18,363 --> 00:24:19,667
Best stay close.

324
00:24:24,371 --> 00:24:26,644
Mr. Harry Potter wishes
to make a withdrawal.

325
00:24:32,218 --> 00:24:35,222
And does Mr. Harry Potter
have his key?

326
00:24:36,489 --> 00:24:38,371
Oh, wait a minute.
Got it here somewhere.

327
00:24:43,207 --> 00:24:44,488
Here is the little devil.

328
00:24:45,221 --> 00:24:47,098
Oh and there is something else as well.

329
00:24:49,775 --> 00:24:51,707
Professor Dumbledore gave me this.

330
00:24:56,893 --> 00:24:58,527
It's about You-Know-What,

331
00:24:58,847 --> 00:25:01,002
in vault... You-Know-Which.

332
00:25:03,325 --> 00:25:04,299
Very well.

333
00:25:10,433 --> 00:25:12,179
Vault 687.

334
00:25:15,170 --> 00:25:16,451
Lamp, please.

335
00:25:26,025 --> 00:25:27,216
Key, please.

336
00:25:50,980 --> 00:25:53,490
Didn't think your mum and dad
will leave you with nothing, now did you?

337
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,878
Vault 713.

338
00:25:58,192 --> 00:25:59,567
What's in there Hagrid?

339
00:25:59,802 --> 00:26:00,922
Can't tell you Harry.

340
00:26:01,325 --> 00:26:02,680
Hogwarts business.

341
00:26:02,704 --> 00:26:04,004
Very secret.

342
00:26:04,398 --> 00:26:05,239
Stand back.

343
00:26:34,071 --> 00:26:36,237
Best not to mention this to anyone Harry.

344
00:26:45,295 --> 00:26:46,968
I still need...

345
00:26:47,498 --> 00:26:48,473
a wand.

346
00:26:49,317 --> 00:26:50,263
A wand?

347
00:26:50,724 --> 00:26:53,013
Well, you will want Ollivanders.
There ain't no place better.

348
00:26:53,642 --> 00:26:55,227
Why don't you run along there and wait.

349
00:26:55,802 --> 00:26:58,036
I just got one more thing I got to do.
Won't be long.

350
00:27:16,577 --> 00:27:17,433
Hello?

351
00:27:21,425 --> 00:27:22,285
Hello?

352
00:27:26,748 --> 00:27:30,449
I wondered when
I would be seeing you, Mr. Potter.

353
00:27:38,903 --> 00:27:41,332
It seems only yesterday,

354
00:27:41,357 --> 00:27:45,646
that your mother and father were
in here buying their first wands.

355
00:27:53,668 --> 00:27:55,052
Here we are.

356
00:28:04,623 --> 00:28:06,084
Give it a wave.

357
00:28:13,708 --> 00:28:15,059
Apparently not.

358
00:28:23,742 --> 00:28:24,989
Perhaps...

359
00:28:27,399 --> 00:28:28,567
this.

360
00:28:36,904 --> 00:28:39,372
No, no, definitely not.

361
00:28:40,411 --> 00:28:41,505
No matter.

362
00:28:48,679 --> 00:28:50,224
I wonder...

363
00:29:19,628 --> 00:29:20,865
Curious.

364
00:29:22,073 --> 00:29:23,869
Very curious.

365
00:29:25,149 --> 00:29:26,092
Sorry,

366
00:29:26,986 --> 00:29:28,431
but what's curious?

367
00:29:29,995 --> 00:29:32,517
I remember every wand
I have ever sold, Mr. Potter.

368
00:29:33,511 --> 00:29:34,803
It so happens,

369
00:29:34,827 --> 00:29:36,244
that the phoenix...

370
00:29:36,559 --> 00:29:39,099
whose tail feather resides in your wand,

371
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:40,885
gave another feather.

372
00:29:41,689 --> 00:29:44,103
Just one other.

373
00:29:44,967 --> 00:29:48,595
It is curious that
you should be destined for this wand...

374
00:29:49,434 --> 00:29:50,652
when its brother...

375
00:29:51,715 --> 00:29:53,871
gave you that scar.

376
00:29:56,963 --> 00:29:58,900
And who owned that wand?

377
00:30:01,190 --> 00:30:03,205
We do not speak his name.

378
00:30:03,981 --> 00:30:06,904
The wand chooses the wizard, Mr. Potter.

379
00:30:07,556 --> 00:30:09,818
It's not always clear why.

380
00:30:11,002 --> 00:30:11,756
But...

381
00:30:12,380 --> 00:30:14,076
I think it is clear...

382
00:30:14,851 --> 00:30:17,459
that we can expect great things from you.

383
00:30:18,850 --> 00:30:19,848
After all,

384
00:30:20,724 --> 00:30:22,849
He-Who-Must-Not-Be-Named...

385
00:30:23,451 --> 00:30:25,201
did great things.

386
00:30:26,101 --> 00:30:27,085
Terrible...

387
00:30:28,790 --> 00:30:29,691
yes...

388
00:30:30,542 --> 00:30:31,780
but great.

389
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:39,282
Harry! Harry!

390
00:30:39,987 --> 00:30:41,313
Happy birthday.

391
00:30:49,503 --> 00:30:50,587
You alright, Harry?

392
00:30:50,961 --> 00:30:52,126
You seem very quiet.

393
00:30:53,519 --> 00:30:55,467
He killed my parents, didn't he?

394
00:30:56,451 --> 00:30:58,006
The one who gave me this.

395
00:30:59,188 --> 00:31:00,388
You know Hagrid.

396
00:31:01,678 --> 00:31:02,967
I know you do.

397
00:31:06,649 --> 00:31:09,915
First, and understand this Harry
because it's very important:

398
00:31:11,497 --> 00:31:13,079
Not all wizards are good.

399
00:31:14,101 --> 00:31:16,512
Some of them go bad.
A few years ago...

400
00:31:16,645 --> 00:31:19,032
there was a one wizard
who went as bad as he can go.

401
00:31:19,180 --> 00:31:20,739
His name was V...

402
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:23,411
His name was V...

403
00:31:24,207 --> 00:31:25,746
Maybe if you wrote it down?

404
00:31:25,848 --> 00:31:27,168
No, I can't spell it.

405
00:31:28,065 --> 00:31:28,958
Alright.

406
00:31:29,924 --> 00:31:30,919
Voldemort.

407
00:31:31,283 --> 00:31:32,400
Voldemort?

408
00:31:36,359 --> 00:31:38,323
It was dark times, Harry. Dark times.

409
00:31:40,911 --> 00:31:43,573
Voldemort started
to gather some followers.

410
00:31:44,203 --> 00:31:46,315
Brought them over to the Dark Side.

411
00:31:48,951 --> 00:31:50,396
Anyone that stood up to him,

412
00:31:50,420 --> 00:31:51,744
ended up dead.

413
00:31:53,142 --> 00:31:55,182
Your parents fought against him.

414
00:31:56,598 --> 00:31:58,806
Nobody lived once
he decided to kill them.

415
00:32:04,503 --> 00:32:05,370
Nobody,

416
00:32:05,717 --> 00:32:06,670
not one.

417
00:32:07,248 --> 00:32:08,436
Except you.

418
00:32:11,773 --> 00:32:12,585
Me?

419
00:32:13,335 --> 00:32:14,629
Voldemort tried to kill...

420
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:15,914
me?

421
00:32:16,405 --> 00:32:16,965
Yes.

422
00:32:17,436 --> 00:32:20,139
That ain't no ordinary cut
on your forehead, Harry.

423
00:32:20,905 --> 00:32:24,222
A mark like that only comes from being
touched by a curse,

424
00:32:24,246 --> 00:32:25,962
and an evil curse at that.

425
00:32:26,819 --> 00:32:27,975
What happened to V...

426
00:32:29,227 --> 00:32:30,444
To You-Know-Who?

427
00:32:31,424 --> 00:32:32,230
Well,

428
00:32:32,405 --> 00:32:33,835
some say he died.

429
00:32:35,165 --> 00:32:36,942
Codswallop, in my opinion.

430
00:32:37,663 --> 00:32:38,403
Nope,

431
00:32:38,770 --> 00:32:40,645
I reckon he is out there still...

432
00:32:41,249 --> 00:32:43,145
too tired to carry on.

433
00:32:44,435 --> 00:32:45,994
But one thing is absolutely certain.

434
00:32:46,552 --> 00:32:49,278
Something about you
stumped him that night.

435
00:32:49,971 --> 00:32:51,583
That's why you are famous.

436
00:32:51,607 --> 00:32:53,973
That's why everybody knows your name.

437
00:32:54,812 --> 00:32:56,953
You are the boy who lived.

438
00:33:07,710 --> 00:33:09,226
What are you looking at?

439
00:33:12,210 --> 00:33:13,859
Blimey, is that the time?

440
00:33:14,317 --> 00:33:15,899
Sorry, Harry, I am gonna have to leave you.

441
00:33:16,180 --> 00:33:17,922
Dumbledore will be wanting his...

442
00:33:18,727 --> 00:33:20,111
Well, he will be wanting to see me.

443
00:33:20,532 --> 00:33:21,487
Now...

444
00:33:21,602 --> 00:33:23,235
your train leaves in 10 minutes.

445
00:33:23,414 --> 00:33:24,532
Here is your ticket.

446
00:33:24,806 --> 00:33:26,618
Stick to it, Harry that's very important.

447
00:33:26,642 --> 00:33:28,009
Stick to your ticket.

448
00:33:32,004 --> 00:33:33,496
Platform 9 3/4?

449
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:35,376
But Hagrid,

450
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:36,836
there must be a mistake.

451
00:33:37,207 --> 00:33:39,223
This says platform 9 3/4.

452
00:33:39,418 --> 00:33:41,597
There is no such thing, is there?

453
00:34:00,953 --> 00:34:01,990
Sorry.

454
00:34:04,365 --> 00:34:05,406
Excuse me.

455
00:34:05,764 --> 00:34:06,732
Excuse me.

456
00:34:07,522 --> 00:34:08,865
Right on your left Madam.

457
00:34:09,157 --> 00:34:10,119
Excuse me Sir.

458
00:34:10,295 --> 00:34:13,084
Can you tell me where
I might find platform 9 3/4?

459
00:34:13,126 --> 00:34:14,374
9 3/4?

460
00:34:14,398 --> 00:34:15,662
Think you are being funny, do you?

461
00:34:15,687 --> 00:34:17,001
9 3/4?
It's the same every year,

462
00:34:17,025 --> 00:34:19,387
packed with Muggles of course.
Come on!

463
00:34:19,571 --> 00:34:21,821
Muggles?
Platform 9 3/4, this way.

464
00:34:28,734 --> 00:34:29,722
Alright Percy,

465
00:34:30,003 --> 00:34:31,174
you first.

466
00:34:41,951 --> 00:34:43,205
Fred, you next.

467
00:34:43,500 --> 00:34:44,862
He is not Fred, I am.

468
00:34:44,886 --> 00:34:47,370
Honestly woman,
you call yourself our mother?

469
00:34:47,395 --> 00:34:49,081
Oh, I am sorry, George.

470
00:34:53,500 --> 00:34:55,121
I am only joking. I am Fred.

471
00:35:01,573 --> 00:35:02,753
Excuse me.

472
00:35:05,282 --> 00:35:06,426
Could, could you tell me...

473
00:35:07,032 --> 00:35:07,993
how to...

474
00:35:08,540 --> 00:35:10,263
How to get onto the platform?

475
00:35:10,287 --> 00:35:11,899
Not to worry, dear.

476
00:35:11,924 --> 00:35:14,623
It's Ron's first time to Hogwarts as well.

477
00:35:14,648 --> 00:35:16,060
Now all you have got to do...

478
00:35:16,554 --> 00:35:18,730
is walk straight at the wall,

479
00:35:18,754 --> 00:35:20,554
between platforms 9 and 10.

480
00:35:20,750 --> 00:35:22,692
Best do it at a bit of a run
if you are nervous.

481
00:35:22,716 --> 00:35:23,794
Good luck.

482
00:36:21,701 --> 00:36:23,086
Excuse me.

483
00:36:23,360 --> 00:36:24,337
Do you mind?

484
00:36:24,867 --> 00:36:26,266
Everywhere else is full.

485
00:36:26,351 --> 00:36:27,391
Not at all.

486
00:36:31,581 --> 00:36:32,762
I am Ron by the way.

487
00:36:32,961 --> 00:36:34,031
Ron Weasley.

488
00:36:34,070 --> 00:36:35,805
I am Harry. Harry Potter.

489
00:36:38,266 --> 00:36:38,976
So...

490
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,125
it's true!

491
00:36:40,411 --> 00:36:41,270
I mean,

492
00:36:41,789 --> 00:36:43,149
do you really have the...

493
00:36:43,539 --> 00:36:44,524
The...
The what?

494
00:36:45,892 --> 00:36:46,977
Scar?

495
00:36:49,848 --> 00:36:51,055
Wicked!

496
00:36:54,487 --> 00:36:56,202
Anything off the trolley, dears?

497
00:36:56,358 --> 00:36:57,537
No thanks.

498
00:36:57,920 --> 00:36:59,047
I am all set.

499
00:37:03,701 --> 00:37:04,927
We will take the lot.

500
00:37:16,912 --> 00:37:18,766
Bertie Bott's Every Flavor Beans?

501
00:37:18,790 --> 00:37:20,530
They mean every flavor.

502
00:37:21,963 --> 00:37:23,646
There is chocolate and peppermint,

503
00:37:24,010 --> 00:37:25,447
and there is also...

504
00:37:25,642 --> 00:37:26,691
spinach,

505
00:37:26,715 --> 00:37:28,447
liver and tripe.

506
00:37:29,689 --> 00:37:32,509
George sweared he got
a bogey flavoured one once!

507
00:37:38,481 --> 00:37:39,962
These are not real
frogs, are they?

508
00:37:40,350 --> 00:37:41,539
It's just a spell.

509
00:37:41,563 --> 00:37:43,554
Besides, it's the cards you want.

510
00:37:43,971 --> 00:37:46,294
Each pack's got a famous witch or wizard.

511
00:37:46,435 --> 00:37:48,242
I have got about 500 myself.

512
00:37:51,034 --> 00:37:52,198
Watch it!

513
00:37:55,600 --> 00:37:56,971
Oh, that's rotten luck.

514
00:37:57,205 --> 00:37:59,565
They ave only got one
good jump in them to begin with.

515
00:38:01,910 --> 00:38:03,144
I have got Dumbledore!

516
00:38:03,479 --> 00:38:05,182
I got about six of him.

517
00:38:07,767 --> 00:38:08,807
Hey, he is gone!

518
00:38:08,965 --> 00:38:11,360
Well, you can't expect him
to hang around all day,

519
00:38:11,384 --> 00:38:12,245
can you?

520
00:38:13,504 --> 00:38:14,780
This is Scabbers by the way.

521
00:38:15,425 --> 00:38:16,660
Pathetic, isn't he?

522
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:18,136
Just a little bit.

523
00:38:18,161 --> 00:38:20,411
Fred gave me a spell as
to turn him yellow.

524
00:38:20,761 --> 00:38:21,800
Want to see?

525
00:38:21,859 --> 00:38:22,647
Yeah.

526
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:32,198
Has anyone seen a toad?

527
00:38:32,675 --> 00:38:34,557
A boy named Neville's lost one.

528
00:38:34,582 --> 00:38:35,516
No.

529
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:37,637
Are you doing magic?

530
00:38:37,661 --> 00:38:38,979
Let's see then.

531
00:38:41,500 --> 00:38:43,643
Sunshine, daisies,

532
00:38:43,789 --> 00:38:45,320
butter mellow.

533
00:38:45,727 --> 00:38:47,601
Turn this stupid fat rat yellow.

534
00:38:51,751 --> 00:38:53,694
Are you sure that's a real spell?

535
00:38:54,678 --> 00:38:56,725
Well, it's not very good, is it?

536
00:38:57,496 --> 00:39:00,592
Of course, I have only tried
a few simple ones myself...

537
00:39:00,903 --> 00:39:02,365
but they ave all worked for me.

538
00:39:07,188 --> 00:39:08,259
For example.

539
00:39:09,650 --> 00:39:11,220
Oculus Reparo.

540
00:39:14,700 --> 00:39:15,809
That's better, isn't it?

541
00:39:18,276 --> 00:39:19,720
Holy cricket,

542
00:39:20,057 --> 00:39:21,760
you are Harry Potter!

543
00:39:22,363 --> 00:39:23,724
I am Hermione Granger.

544
00:39:24,128 --> 00:39:25,101
And...

545
00:39:25,265 --> 00:39:26,303
you are?

546
00:39:26,900 --> 00:39:28,312
I am, Ron Weasley.

547
00:39:28,657 --> 00:39:29,657
Pleasure.

548
00:39:30,298 --> 00:39:32,191
You two better change into robes.

549
00:39:32,215 --> 00:39:34,009
I expect we will be arriving soon.

550
00:39:39,427 --> 00:39:41,450
You have got dirt on your nose, by the way.

551
00:39:41,801 --> 00:39:42,793
Did you know?

552
00:39:43,034 --> 00:39:44,004
Just there.

553
00:39:57,344 --> 00:39:59,135
Right then!
First years!

554
00:39:59,531 --> 00:40:00,789
This way please!

555
00:40:01,295 --> 00:40:03,306
Come on now, first years don't be shy.

556
00:40:04,132 --> 00:40:06,085
